## Setup

This project supports two coordination modes — see `WORKTREE_PATTERNS.md` at repo root for the full decision tree, setup recipes, and failure modes.

### Mode 1 — Single checkout (default)

All leads work in the same physical folder on the `{{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}` branch (or feature branches per change cluster). File ownership enforced by `.claude/agents/<name>.md` persona instruction.

**To start a lead session:**
1. Open a new Claude Code terminal in `<project root>`.
2. Invoke `/aria` or `/bram` or `/cleo` (project skill at `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`).
3. The persona system prompt (`.claude/agents/<name>.md`) makes the agent operate as that named lead.

Multiple leads CAN run concurrently in separate terminal windows — file ownership separation prevents collisions. Use Mode 1 for short builds (≤5 days) and small teams (1-2 concurrent leads).

### Mode 2 — Per-lead worktrees (escalate when Mode 1 bites)

When 2+ leads do sustained parallel code work over multiple days, create per-lead git worktrees with junctions to share `.project/` and `.claude/`. Setup recipe in `WORKTREE_PATTERNS.md`. In short:

```bash
# From the main checkout
git worktree add ../<project>-aria -b crt/aria-day1
git worktree add ../<project>-bram -b crt/bram-day1

# In each worktree, junction the coordination dirs
cd ../<project>-aria
cmd //c mklink /J .project ..\\<project>\\.project    # Windows
cmd //c mklink /J .claude  ..\\<project>\\.claude
# Unix: ln -s ../<project>/.project .project ; ln -s ../<project>/.claude .claude
```

Then open Cursor on the lead's worktree and run their slash command from there. **Always remove junctions BEFORE `git worktree remove`** (see WORKTREE_PATTERNS.md "Failure modes").

### Background-mode dispatch (works in either mode)

Tate can dispatch leads from its main session via the `Agent` tool with `run_in_background: true`. Two `Agent` calls in one message → both leads run in parallel:

```python
Agent(subagent_type: aria, prompt: "[lead-specific kickoff brief]", run_in_background: true)
Agent(subagent_type: bram, prompt: "[lead-specific kickoff brief]", run_in_background: true)
```

