## Rules (apply to every lead)

1. Read `.gauntlet/{{PROJECT_SLUG}}/in-flight.md` (this file) before any edit.
2. Read your handoff (`.gauntlet/{{PROJECT_SLUG}}/handoffs/<name>-handoff.md`) before any edit.
3. Read your kickoff (`.gauntlet/{{PROJECT_SLUG}}/kickoff/<name>.md`) before any edit.
4. Restate to the user before any edit: identity, mission, what's risky, your next concrete edit.
5. Wait for user confirmation before any edit.
6. **Do not edit files outside your ownership.** RAISE if a task requires it.
7. **Do not weaken architectural commitments** without sign-off (schemas, security gates, cost guards, trust gates).
8. **No secrets / API keys / HMAC tokens / cloud credentials** in any committed file. Use `.env`.
9. **No raw sensitive data** (PHI / PII / patient data / etc.) in any committed file. Synthetic / sentinel data only.
10. Update In Flight (below) when you START or FINISH a session.
11. Write/update your handoff file before `/clear` or exit.

